article.headline: Kentucky State 72, Southern 60
article.story: BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) -- Jerimie Collier had 23 points to lead Southern University to a 72-60 win over Kentucky State on Friday night. Collier was 7-of-18 from the floor and 8-of-10 from the free throw line. Peter Cipriano added 21 points for Southern (1-0), hitting 8-of-12 from the field and 5-of-10 from the line. Anthony Diggs led Kentucky State (0-1) in scoring with 18 points and Kyle Allen added 15, hitting 4-of-10 from the 3-point range. Diggs also had five assists and five rebounds. Kentucky State led 36-32 at halftime on 44 percent shooting from the floor. But Southern outshot Kentucky State 44 percent to 18 percent in the second half. Southern outrebounded Kentucky State 55-42 with Cipriano pulling in 13 rebounds and Jarvis Vaughn 10. Kentucky State had 20 turnovers to Southern's 18 and Kentucky State committed 27 fouls to Southern's 19.
